## Complexity Analysis

### BFS (what-can-i-cook)

Time Complexity: O(V + E)  
Space Complexity: O(V)  

Where V is the number of nodes and E is the number of edges.

---

### Jaccard Similarity

Time Complexity: O(n + m)  
Space Complexity: O(1)  

Where n and m are sizes of ingredient sets.

---

### Recipe Matching

Time Complexity: O(R × I)  

Where R is the number of recipes and I is the average number of ingredients.

---

### HashMap Lookup

Time Complexity: O(1) (average)

---

### Filter by Tag

Time Complexity: O(R)

---

### Add Recipe

Time Complexity: O(I + T)

Where I is number of ingredients and T is number of tags.

